articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian and Ukrainian negotiators will meet in Istanbul for their first peace talks in more than three years as both sides come under pressure from U.S. President Donald Trump to end Europe's deadliest conflict since World War Two.
articles.title: Russia and Ukraine to hold first direct peace talks in over three years

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Friday the United Arab Emirates and the United States have agreed to create a path for the Gulf country to buy some of the most advanced artificial intelligence semiconductors from U.S. companies.
articles.title: UAE and US agree on path for Abu Dhabi to buy most advanced AI chips, Trump says

articles.author: Jessica Donati, Emma Farge, Ammu Kannampilly, Jonathan Landay
articles.description: The food stocks have been stuck inside four U.S. government warehouses since the Trump administration's decision in January to cut global aid programs.
articles.title: Exclusive: US aid cuts leave food for millions mouldering in storage

articles.author: Sarita Singh, Krishna N. Das, Aftab Ahmed, Charlotte Greenfield, Ariba Shahid
articles.description: New Delhi suspended its participation in the Indus Waters Treaty of 1960 shortly after 26 civilians in Indian Kashmir were killed in what India called an act of terror.
articles.title: Exclusive: India weighs plan to slash Pakistan water supply with new Indus river project

articles.author: Isabel Teles, Ana Mano
articles.description: Brazil, the world's largest poultry exporter, confirmed its first outbreak of avian influenza on a commercial farm in a statement from the Agriculture Ministry on Friday, raising the prospect of restrictions from trade partners.
articles.title: Brazil confirms first outbreak of avian influenza on commercial farm

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A Thai construction tycoon and 14 others surrendered to police on Friday over a building collapse that killed nearly a hundred workers during a powerful earthquake in March, authorities said.
articles.title: Thai construction tycoon and 14 others surrender to police over fatal Bangkok tower collapse

articles.author: Antonio Bronic
articles.description: The fortresses and cobbled streets of the ancient Croatian town of Dubrovnik are often crowded with tourists eager to visit the locations from the Game of Thrones television series or the Star Wars: The Last Jedi film.
articles.title: Croatia's Game of Thrones filming sites face threat from Trump tariffs

articles.author: Laurie Chen, Joe Cash
articles.description: Britain's long-awaited audit of relations with China is expected to be released in early June, two sources familiar with the matter told Reuters, as London seeks to improve commercial ties with Beijing while guarding against perceived security threats.
articles.title: Britain's audit on China relations to be released in June, sources say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The end of preferential trade with the European Union in June could deprive Ukraine of 3.5 billion euros ($3.92 billion) in annual revenue, a hole other markets will be unable to fill, a senior Ukrainian lawmaker said on Friday.
articles.title: Ukraine may lose 3.5 billion euros a year if EU trade privileges end, lawmaker says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: U.S. President Donald Trump announced deals worth hundreds of billions of dollars between the United States and Gulf nations during his four-day tour of the oil- and gas-rich Middle East.
articles.title: Trump's Gulf tour sparks AI, finance and energy deals
